column1: #Plot cover is canopy cover and totals >100% because of layers

# In 2025 For all collectors except Jane, "Grass" plot cover includes all grass-like monocots like grasses, sedges, bulrushes, rushes, though 100% is max listed under "grass" these are often multi-layered within the plot.

#Jane only included true grasses in "Grass" cover and sedges/rushes as a separate type of cover. these should be adjusted for consistency.  one approach could be adding grass + sedge/rush, but overlapping layers could make the total grass cover > 100%.
# "Thatch" includes mulch and non-bare but non-vegetated ground cover visible at soil level
